But the scale at which this kind of “household service” existed in Britain

00:02:24.702 --> 00:02:29.522
in the late 19th century and early 20th century is quite staggering.

00:02:30.912 --> 00:02:37.102
In 1901, the population of the UK was just under 37,000,000.

00:02:38.222 --> 00:02:47.862
Of this, a whopping 1.5 million so 4% of the total population, worked as domestic servants.

